      "inheritance_hierarchy": "LiquidInfrastructureERC20 inherits OpenZeppelin ERC20, ERC20Burnable, Ownable, ERC721Holder, ReentrancyGuard. LiquidInfrastructureNFT inherits OpenZeppelin ERC721 and custom OwnableApprovableERC721 (which itself inherits Context and ERC721). OwnableApprovableERC721 provides access-control modifiers based on ERC721 ownership/approval for a specific tokenId.",
      "external_dependencies": [
        "OpenZeppelin: ERC20, ERC20Burnable, IERC20, ERC721, ERC721Holder, Ownable, ReentrancyGuard, Context, Math",
        "External protocol/module dependency (off-chain / Cosmos integration assumption): x/microtx module reacts to LiquidInfrastructureNFT events TryRecover and reads thresholds; not enforced on-chain"
      ],
      "upgrade_patterns": "None (constructors used; no Initializable/UUPS/Transparent/Diamond patterns present).",
      "access_control_structure": "LiquidInfrastructureERC20 uses OpenZeppelin Ownable (single admin) for management functions and relies on HolderAllowlist gating in _beforeTokenTransfer for KYC. Distributions/withdrawals are generally public but are constrained by distribution lock and period logic. LiquidInfrastructureNFT uses ERC721 ownership of AccountId=1 as the controlling authority; additionally allows approved operators (ERC721 approvals) to set thresholds and withdraw balances. No AccessControl roles, pausing, or upgrade admin roles."
    },
